The pediatrician's involvement in prevention and treatment of oral disease in medically compromised children.
 Significant oral health problems are associated with medical, physical, or mental disorders that occur in children.
 The pediatrician has the opportunity through early intervention to set the tone for a health care practice that will improve the quality of life for many disadvantaged children.
 When the pediatrician and pediatric dentist work hand in hand, the children can often expect a happy, healthy future.
